The Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, has said there is no reason for the All Progressives Congress, APC, to remain in power in 2023. The Party’s Chairman in Jigawa State, Hon. Babandi Ibrahim Gumel stated this on Thursday when he received a delegation of Atiku 2023 campaign team at the Party’s headquarters in Dutse. He said looking at the current situation the country is going through, there is no reason for the APC to continue to remain in power. “What is happening in Jigawa State and Nigeria in general is a clear testimony that the APC has failed Nigerians. “Therefore, there is no reason for the APC to continue to remain in power come 2023 general election. “The APC is going no where, it is sinking and will continue to sink until 2023 election,” he said. The Chairman urged Nigerians to do away with all the APC lies and propaganda and vote the party out in the coming election. Why I want APC to remain in power for long time – Buhari